content: Hey y'all, sorry for late notice, but I'm not available this coming Thursday for a meeting
Not sure if we want to skip or move it? I'm somewhat inclined to skip
I’m okay with skipping this weeks. Will we skip the next meeting after that? As I believe that’s the same day as RustConf.
maybe we can try to schedule for another time, or do some more async work
Happy to record key aspects of async or sync discussions as informal-nonminutes if useful

Also, if useful can attend one or more of the meetings with libs/compiler and try to take notes in realtime (or after the fact if meetings on Zulip). I am aware I am not prompt, working to improve this. Also, https://github.com/rust-lang/wg-governance/blob/master/minutes/2020.07.23.md may be useful in planning, happy to adjust if needed.
